Title: Georg Fischer 22L ABS EPDM safe double union ball valve 2"
Description: Suitable for use in industrial setings, this TP double union lever operated ball valve includes 2" solvent weld connections and a locking end for easy adjustment of torque on the ball in the valve, depending on water pressure. The handle of this valve can be removed and used as a spanner to tighten the locking end. A ball valve is a type of quarter-turn valve featuring a hollow, perforated ball that pivots to control the flow of a fluid. The valve is open when the ball's hole is in line with flow and closed when pivoted to 90°. The long lasting reliability of ball valves makes them popular in a wide range of settings.
